Image Enhancement Techniques for Experimental Fluid Mechanics

1. Input image

A = imread('side view first.png');
figure(1);
imshow(A);
Warning: Image is too big to fit on screen; displaying at 33%
title('Original input image','FontSize',18);
A1= rgb2gray(A);

2. Histogram Equalization

histequalize= histeq(A1);
figure(2);
suptitle('Histogram Equalization of the image')
subplot(2,2,1);
imshow(A1);
subplot(2,2,2);
imhist(A1);
subplot(2,2,3);
imshow(histequalize);
subplot(2,2,4);
imhist(histequalize);

3. Average filter

h=ones(9,9)/81;
avgfil= imfilter(histequalize,h);
figure (3);
imshow(avgfil);
Warning: Image is too big to fit on screen; displaying at 33%
title('Average filtered image','FontSize',18);

4. Edge detection

figure(4);
subplot(2,2,1);
imshow(A1);
title('Original image')
subplot(2,2,2);
b = edge(A1);
imshow(b)
title('Inbuilt edge detection')
subplot(2,2,3);
c=edge(A1,'canny');
imshow(c);
title('Canny edge detector')
subplot(2,2,4);
d = bwmorph(c,'dilate',2);
imshow(d);
title('Dilated edge detector');

5. Exporting image

figure(5);
a = imshow(d);
Warning: Image is too big to fit on screen; displaying at 33%
saveas(a,'dilated.png');
